'''Curufinwë''' was the [[father-name]] of the [[Noldor|Noldorin Elf]] [[Fëanor]]. It consisted on the noun ''[[curu]]'' ("skill") attached to the name of ''[[Finwë]]''.<ref>{{S|Index}}, entry "Fëanor"</ref> 

Fëanor was first called ''Finwion'' ("Finwë's son"), but when he soon showed his talent, it was changed to ''Curufinwë''.<ref>{{MR|P3II3a}}, p. 217</ref> This name was also given to his son [[Curufin]], whose [[Sindarin]] name is a condensed form. The short form was '''''Curvo'''''.<ref>{{PM|Shibboleth}}, p. 352</ref>

